 The City Diary
																																																																																		The Calcutta Municipal Corporation will keep a special vigil on 12 ghats and 18 ponds on Saturday and Sunday to ensure Kali idols are immersed in the enclosures reserved for the purpose. Civic officials said that like Durga puja, the accessories of the goddess, too, have to be kept in baskets set up for their disposal.																																																		One person was arrested at Calcutta airport on Friday morning on charges of travelling with a fake passport. Paramjit Singh, 31, a resident of Amritsar, arrived at Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose International Airport from Singapore on a Singapore Airlines flight. The immigration authorities realised that his passport was a fake. Officials said his passport did not have his real name. His real identity could be detected from his driving licence and credit card. Later, he was handed over to police.																																																		Around 100 people were arrested at various railway stations of Eastern Railways Sealdah division on Friday. According to Government Railway Police officers, the persons were arrested on charges of criminal activities, including snatching and getting into brawls on platforms.																																																		Four labourers were seriously injured when a sand-laden truck headed for the city overturned near Rahara, on the citys northern fringes, on Friday. According to police, the driver of the vehicle, who is absconding, lost control due to overloading. The truck hit a roadside railing before overturning. The vehicle has been impounded.																																																		Two Calcutta High Court judges  Justice Pinaki Chandra Ghose and Justice Kalyanjyoti Sengupta  on Friday visited Presidency jail to hear pleas from inmates on decreasing the period of their sentences to mark National Legal Services Day. Jail superintendent Kamal Mukherjee said the judges heard the pleas of over 200 prisoners.							TO LIONS CLUB OF CALCUTTA (TOLLYGUNGE) for installing two tubewells in the Amta area
